## Summary

We are currently [using `string option` for `Command.command`](https://github.com/fsharp/FsAutoComplete/blob/master/src/LanguageServerProtocol/LanguageServerProtocol.fs#L1429
):
```fsharp
    type Command = {
        /// Title of the command, like `save`.
        Title: string

        /// The identifier of the actual command handler.
        Command: string option

        /// Arguments that the command handler should be
        /// invoked with.
        Arguments: JToken[] option
    }
```

but the [LSP spec](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/specification-current/#command) says it's not optional:

```typescript
interface Command {
	/**
	 * Title of the command, like `save`.
	 */
	title: string;
	/**
	 * The identifier of the actual command handler.
	 */
	command: string;
	/**
	 * Arguments that the command handler should be
	 * invoked with.
	 */
	arguments?: any[];
}

```

